# Frontend README (`frontend/README.md`)

## Vet Chatbot Frontend & SDK

This is the **frontend UI and embeddable SDK** for Vet Chatbot.

You can:

- Run it as a normal React app
- Build it as a **script SDK**
- Use it on any website

---

## Technologies Used

- React
- Vite
- Tailwind CSS
- JavaScript
- CDN (Vercel)

---

## Folder Structure

```
frontend/chatbot-sdk/
â”‚
â”œâ”€â”€ sdk/
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ index.jsx
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ App.jsx
â”‚   â””â”€â”€ style.css
â”‚
â”œâ”€â”€ dist/
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ vet-chatbot-sdk.iife.js
â”‚   â””â”€â”€ vet-chatbot-sdk.css
â”‚
â”œâ”€â”€ vite.sdk.config.js
â”œâ”€â”€ tailwind.config.js
â”œâ”€â”€ package.json
â””â”€â”€ README.md
```

---

## Setup Frontend (Local)

### Go to frontend folder

```bash
cd frontend/chatbot-sdk
```

### Install packages

```bash
npm install
```

### Start frontend

```bash
npm run dev
```

Open browser:

```
http://localhost:5173
```

---

## Tailwind Setup (Already Done)

Tailwind is already configured.
If you see UI styled â†’ Tailwind is working

---

## Build SDK File

### Build SDK

```bash
npm run build:sdk
```

### package.json script

```json
{
  "scripts": {
    "build:sdk": "vite build --config vite.sdk.config.js"
  }
}
```

After build:

```
dist/
â”œâ”€â”€ vet-chatbot-sdk.iife.js
â”œâ”€â”€ vet-chatbot-sdk.css
```

---

## Use SDK on Any Website

### Add CSS

```html
<link
  rel="stylesheet"
  href="https://vet-chat-bot-liard.vercel.app/vet-chatbot-sdk.css"
/>
```

### Add Script

```html
<script src="https://vet-chat-bot-liard.vercel.app/vet-chatbot-sdk.iife.js"></script>
```

### Done

Chatbot will appear automatically.

---

## Test SDK Locally

Create `index.html`:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>SDK Test</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="./dist/vet-chatbot-sdk.css" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>Hello</h1>
    <script src="./dist/vet-chatbot-sdk.iife.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>
```

Open using Live Server.

